    "recap_headline": "Troy University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "MONTGOMERY, Ala.\n- Troy's offensive hot streak continued on Tuesday with an 11-2 win over Alabama State at the Wheeler-Watkins Baseball Complex.\nThe Trojans (9-11) outhit the Hornets (9-10) 10-7, scoring eight of their 11 runs off ASU starter Jaxon Bishop in his 4-plus innings. Among the Trojans' key hits were a two-run homer by\nSteven Meier\nin the third and a two-RBI triple by Sun Belt Player of the Week\nJimmy Janicki\nin the fifth.\nJosh Pyne\nand\nSean Darnell\neach added a pair of singles, while\nHouston Markham\n, whose grandfather,\nHouston Markham\nJr., was the head football coach at ASU from 1987-99, doubled twice while also adding an HBP.\nOn the mound, Troy's pitching staff recorded 12 strikeouts while issuing just four walks, and at the plate, the offense showed strong discipline with only four strikeouts while drawing eight free passes -\u00a0 four walks and four hit-by-pitches.\nFreshman right-hander\nMatt Dill\nset the tone for the Trojans in his first career start. The Dayton, Tenn., native pitched four innings with one run on four hits, striking out three Hornets without a walk. Dill was scoreless through his first three innings of work before a trio of singles scored ASU's first run in the fourth.\nThe Troy bullpen allowed just one run in five innings in relief. Two-way player\nDrew Nelson\nmade his first appearance on the mound this season, striking the first two hitters he faced before an HBP, a single and a wild pitch led to an ASU run.\nNoah Thigpen\ntossed two hitless innings with three strikeouts, while lefty\nHayden Smith\nand righty\nBrady Richardson\nheld the Hornets scoreless in the eighth and ninth.\nNotables\nTroy moves to 35-5 all-time against Alabama State. The Trojans have won 18 straight over the Hornets, including eight straight under head coach\nSkylar Meade\n.\nTroy's pitching staff struck out 12 hitters, one shy of its season high.\nFreshman RHP\nMatt Dill\nmade his first career start, going a career-long 4.0 innings.\nTwo-way player\nDrew Nelson\nmade his first appearance on the mound this season. He pitched one inning, striking out two, while allowing one run, one hit and one HBP.\nHayden Smith's\ntwo strikeouts matched his season high.\nSteven Meier's\ntwo-run homer in the third inning was his second home run of the season. It traveled 390 feet with an exit velocity of 101 MPH.\nJosh Pyne\nextended his hitting streak to seven games, going 2-for-5. He's batting .367 during that stretch.\nJimmy Janicki\nwent 2-for-5 with a double, a triple and two RBIs. His 11 multi-hit games and six multi-RBI games both lead the team.\nJanicki extended his hitting streak to five games. He's hitting .455 during that stretch.\nHouston Markham\nwent 2-for-3 with a pair of doubles and an HBP, recording his first multi-hit game of the season.\nQuotables\nHead Coach\nSkylar Meade\n\"You've got to be aggressive on the mound, and we did that. We're going to continue to push the competitive nature of our arms because I think that's going to be their honey hole, their sweet spot to be their very best. We will turn over every leaf to find how we can do that, and I think you're starting to see some guys turn that into the direction we need as Trojans.\"\nRHP\nMatt Dill\n\"I was really excited to go and get my first start. I've been working towards that. Having those longer bullpen outings has been pretty helpful and boosted my confidence to get out there and start.\"\nNext Up\nTroy returns to Sun Belt action at No. 12 Southern Miss for a three-game series Friday through Sunday."
  },
